{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-03-22T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Water has always shaped human survival, but moments come when simply flowing along is no longer enough—we have to protect the systems that carry us forward. Few places capture that urgency like Lake Tanganyika, set deep within the Great Rift Valley of eastern Africa. Seen from space, it stretches like a narrow ribbon about 676 kilometres long, linking Tanzania, Burundi, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia. At the shoreline, it's a 10-million-year-old rift basin, formed as the Earth's crust slowly pulled apart.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TanganyikaWater_ROW4763595612_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TanganyikaWater_ROW4763595612_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lake Tanganyika, Africa","Copyright":"© BEST-BACKGROUNDS/NASA/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260322_TanganyikaWater\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lake+Tanganyika&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260322_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260322_TanganyikaWater"},"Ssd":"20260322","Name":"TanganyikaWater","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4763595612","FullDateString":"22 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If Earth ran on routine check-ups, wetlands like the Danube Delta, shared between Romania and Ukraine, would top the list. This vast landscape quietly filters water, absorbs floodwaters and shelters wildlife on a remarkable scale. Covering more than 5,800 square kilometres, the Danube Delta Biosphere Reserve is one of Europe's largest and best-preserved wetlands. It's where the Danube River finally slows down, splitting into channels, lakes, reed beds and marshes before meeting the Black Sea. Letea Forest, featured in today's image, is a part of this vast biosphere.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LeteaForest_ROW4397618654_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LeteaForest_ROW4397618654_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Letea Forest, Danube Delta, Romania","Copyright":"© Wild Wonders of Europe/Widstrand/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260321_LeteaForest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Danube+Delta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260321_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260321_LeteaForest"},"Ssd":"20260321","Name":"LeteaForest","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4397618654","FullDateString":"21 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A white snowdrop feels like spring's quiet debut. No fanfare, no fuss—just a small flower daring to appear as the season begins to turn. Snowdrops are among the earliest bloomers, often pushing through frozen soil, leaf litter and even light snow. How do they manage it? Their nodding, bell-shaped flowers protect pollen from cold rain, while antifreeze-like compounds in their cells help them tolerate frost. Delicate-looking, yes. Fragile? Not at all.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringSnowdrops_ROW7920205293_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringSnowdrops_ROW7920205293_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Snowdrops in spring","Copyright":"© klagyivik/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260320_SpringSnowdrops\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galanthus+flower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260320_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260320_SpringSnowdrops"},"Ssd":"20260320","Name":"SpringSnowdrops","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7920205293","FullDateString":"20 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"An egg-laying mammal. No teeth. Reptilian gait. Built-in body armour. If the short-beaked echidna sounds like a checklist of contradictions, that's because it is—and it owns it. Native to Australia, Tasmania and parts of New Guinea, it's one of the few surviving monotremes, or mammals that lay eggs. Despite the headlines, it still qualifies as a mammal: it has fur, produces milk and is warm-blooded. The twist? Milk is released through specialised skin patches rather than nipples, leaving the young to lap it up.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EchidnaAustralia_ROW4548583116_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EchidnaAustralia_ROW4548583116_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Short-beaked echidna, Adelaide Hills, Australia","Copyright":"© Etienne Littlefair/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260319_EchidnaAustralia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Short-beaked+echidna&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260319_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260319_EchidnaAustralia"},"Ssd":"20260319","Name":"EchidnaAustralia","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4548583116","FullDateString":"19 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Tom McCall Waterfront Park, a 12.5-hectare urban oasis along the Willamette River in Portland, Oregon, is one of the city's most beloved green spaces. Each spring—typically from mid-March to early April—it transforms into a sea of soft pink and white as cherry blossoms bloom. These vibrant trees along scenic walking paths offer a peaceful escape in the heart of the city. The park also features notable landmarks like Salmon Street Springs, an interactive fountain with numerous water jets, and the Portland Saturday Market, a favourite local destination.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PortlandBlossoms_ROW4378783991_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PortlandBlossoms_ROW4378783991_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Cherry blossoms at Tom McCall Waterfront Park, Portland, Oregon, USA","Copyright":"© Eric Vogt/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260318_PortlandBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tom+McCall+Waterfront+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260318_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260318_PortlandBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260318","Name":"PortlandBlossoms","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4378783991","FullDateString":"18 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, we find ourselves in County Donegal in the northwest of Ireland. Grianan of Aileach, a stone ringfort—dating from the Iron Age to the early Middle Ages—linked to the Kings of Aileach and the Northern Uí Néill, stands here. The fort crowns Greenan Mountain and served as a ceremonial and strategic stronghold. Archaeological evidence suggests the site had importance long before the current walls rose in the 6th or 7th century.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DonegalFort_ROW4126307625_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DonegalFort_ROW4126307625_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Grianan of Aileach ring fort, Donegal, Ireland","Copyright":"© Lukassek/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260317_DonegalFort\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grianan+of+Aileach+ring+fort+Donegal&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260317_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260317_DonegalFort"},"Ssd":"20260317","Name":"DonegalFort","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4126307625","FullDateString":"17 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If Rio de Janeiro were a story, today's image would be one of its most iconic chapters. It captures the essence of a metropolis founded on 1 March 1565 to protect Guanabara Bay and control the trade of brazilwood. Since then, it has evolved from a military settlement into a cultural centre, from a strategic port into a national symbol. The city has faced invasions, fires and major political shifts, yet has repeatedly turned challenges into urban expression. Today, the capital of the state of Rio de Janeiro is among the most recognisable cityscapes in the world.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AnivRio_ROW3862828341_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AnivRio_ROW3862828341_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Cable car and Sugarloaf Mountain, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil","Copyright":"© f11photo/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260316_AnivRio\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sugarloaf+Mountain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260316_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260316_AnivRio"},"Ssd":"20260316","Name":"AnivRio","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3862828341","FullDateString":"16 mrt., 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Peggy's Cove is a small yet captivating village on the rugged coast of Nova Scotia that offers a glimpse of life by the sea. The village's most famous landmark is Peggy's Point Lighthouse—also known as Peggy's Cove Lighthouse—first established in 1868 and replaced by the current structure in 1915. For over a century, it has guided ships through the ever-changing Atlantic waters, serving as a timeless symbol of coastal life. The surrounding landscape, with its windswept beauty and crashing waves, feels almost untouched by time.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PeggysLighthouse_ROW0925207018_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PeggysLighthouse_ROW0925207018_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Peggy's Point Lighthouse, Atlantic Coast, Nova Scotia, Canada","Copyright":"© Prashanth Bala/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260329_PeggysLighthouse\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Peggys+Point+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260329_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260329_PeggysLighthouse"},"Ssd":"20260329","Name":"PeggysLighthouse","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0925207018","FullDateString":"29 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The African buffalo, a powerful and imposing creature, roams the savannas and wetlands of Tanzania, particularly within the Ngorongoro Conservation Area (NCA). Known for their large, curved horns and massive size, they are one of Africa's 'Big Five' (buffalo, elephant, leopard, rhino, lion) and are widely respected for their strength and resilience. The NCA, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, offers a dramatic and ecologically rich setting for observing these formidable herbivores.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.CapeBuffalo_ROW0708366233_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.CapeBuffalo_ROW0708366233_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"African buffalo, Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania","Copyright":"© jesuss8/500px/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260328_CapeBuffalo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=African+buffalo&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260328_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260328_CapeBuffalo"},"Ssd":"20260328","Name":"CapeBuffalo","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0708366233","FullDateString":"28 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"This is the kind of landscape that makes maps feel suddenly more interesting. Evening settles quietly over Maligne Lake in Jasper National Park, Alberta. As temperatures drop, the surface stills, mirroring snow-dusted peaks that formed during the last Ice Age. Stretching about 22 kilometres, the lake owes its existence to glacial movement that carved the valley and left behind meltwater basins. Today, cold, oxygen-rich freshwater sustains ecosystems that include species such as lake trout and mountain whitefish. Boat cruises and paddling routes offer one of the best ways to view Spirit Island, the small but widely photographed landmark featured in the image.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_ROW4443502358_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_ROW4443502358_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Aurora over Spirit Island on Maligne Lake, Jasper National Park, Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© Mumemories/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260327_AuroraIsland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Maligne+Lake+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260327_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260327_AuroraIsland"},"Ssd":"20260327","Name":"AuroraIsland","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4443502358","FullDateString":"27 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Running along the remote southwest coast of Vancouver Island, the West Coast Trail is one of the country's most legendary hikes. Located in British Columbia's Pacific Rim National Park Reserve, the trail stretches about 76 kilometres through rainforest, beaches and rocky shoreline. It was established in 1907 as a lifesaving route for shipwreck survivors along what sailors once called the 'Graveyard of the Pacific.'","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LoganCreek_ROW8107496948_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LoganCreek_ROW8107496948_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Logan Creek Suspension Bridge, West Coast Trail, British Columbia, Canada","Copyright":"© Tandem Stock/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260326_LoganCreek\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=West+Coast+Trail+hike&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260326_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260326_LoganCreek"},"Ssd":"20260326","Name":"LoganCreek","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8107496948","FullDateString":"26 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Manatees may seem slow and sleepy, but they have some surprising tricks under the surface. For starters, they are one of the few mammals that constantly replace their teeth. As old molars wear down from chewing gritty seagrass, new ones slowly roll forward like a conveyor belt—handy for an animal that eats for up to eight hours a day.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ManateeSpring_ROW7760366755_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ManateeSpring_ROW7760366755_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Juvenile manatees in a freshwater spring, Crystal River, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Gregory Sweeney/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260325_ManateeSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Manatee&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260325_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260325_ManateeSpring"},"Ssd":"20260325","Name":"ManateeSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7760366755","FullDateString":"25 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When mist drifts across Königssee Lake, located in Bavaria, Germany, in the early morning, the landscape feels almost timeless. The long, narrow mountain lake lies in south-eastern Bavaria, cradled between the steep rock faces of the Berchtesgaden Alps. Large parts of the lake lie within Berchtesgaden National Park, Germany's only Alpine national park, where nature is largely allowed to develop without human interference.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KoenigsseeFog_ROW4902303534_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KoenigsseeFog_ROW4902303534_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Königssee Lake, Bavaria, Germany","Copyright":"© EyeEm Mobile GmbH/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260324_KoenigsseeFog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Konigssee+Lake+Bavaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260324_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260324_KoenigsseeFog"},"Ssd":"20260324","Name":"KoenigsseeFog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4902303534","FullDateString":"24 mrt., 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The strength of nature is nowhere more evident than in powerful storms. Scary? Yes. Fascinating? Even more so. Learning to understand and respect these forces is how people learn to live alongside them. The image of lightning over saguaro cacti captures that balance perfectly. The Sonoran Desert, spanning 260,000 square kilometres across the United States and Mexico, may appear dry and still, but it hosts one of North America's most dynamic desert climates.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_ROW5466478182_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_ROW5466478182_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lightning storm over saguaro cacti, Sonoran Desert, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Jack Dykinga/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sonoran+Desert+Arizona&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260323_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm"},"Ssd":"20260323","Name":"SonoranStorm","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5466478182","FullDateString":"23 mrt., 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Afbeelding van de dag","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Meer informatie","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Doneer nu","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Snel feit:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Recente startpagina-afbeeldingen","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Afbeelding startpagina voor {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"Op deze dag in de geschiedenis","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Op deze dag in {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Bing-startpagina van vandaag delen","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Download deze afbeelding. U mag deze afbeelding alleen gebruiken als achtergrond.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Deze afbeelding downloaden","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"Deze afbeelding kan niet worden gedownload als bureaubladachtergrond.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TE